First compute the product:  
\[
-\,\frac{9}{10}\cdot\frac{8}{15}
=-\frac{9\cdot8}{10\cdot15}
=-\frac{72}{150}
=-\frac{12}{25}.
\]  
Then add \(0.25=\tfrac14=\tfrac{25}{100}\).  Write \(-\tfrac{12}{25}\) as \(-\tfrac{48}{100}\) and add:
\[
-\frac{48}{100}+\frac{25}{100}
=-\frac{23}{100}.
\]
Answer: \(\displaystyle -\frac{23}{100}.\)
